{"ts":"2026-06-26T22:13:36.337Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Visualizing the Nodes**\n\nI'm now detailing visual elements for each node type: trigger, agent reasoning, knowledge graph, tool action, human review, governance check, output, and control center monitoring. For \"Trigger,\" I'm thinking a lightning bolt or play icon in cyan or blue, while \"Agent Reasoning\" could have sparkles or a brain icon. I'm focusing on consistency in the look and feel.\n\nI'm developing a purple/fuchsia theme for the Knowledge Graph nodes, represented by network nodes or a database icon, focusing on querying semantic relations and vector embeddings. For Tool Action, I'm going with an orange/amber color scheme, a wrench or terminal icon, highlighting API executions. Human Review nodes will have a yellow/gold theme with a user shield or checkmark icon, signifying human validation. Governance Checks will be emerald/mint, using a lock or shield icon for privacy and compliance. Output nodes will be teal/green, a document outbox or export icon. Finally, Control Center Monitoring will use a red/crimson theme with a pulse radar or eye icon, to indicate log shipping and uptime.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
